comment: That was the real Fiona. Underneath all of that power, cold heartedness and anger was really a nice woman who lived her entire life alone, unloved and disappointed by everyone she met.
Watching Coven season now and the moment Fiona tells the lady she would make it to her daughter's wedding moved me to tears. Best scene so far. So deep and almost unexpected but yea....
This makes me cry every time
Jessica Lange is so good in this scene
